g.text: - So before jumping into the containerization lets understand "Virtual Machines" First.
- So Problem with Using Virtual Machines Was, we were not using the resources of that
- Suppose we have a virtual machine with 100GB RAM and 200 Processors, But our app
is only using 28GB RAM and 18 Processors, So this is underutilization of resources.
- The each virtual machine we create have its own Operating System.
- Also, Managing the On premises or Physical Virtual machine in your own data centers,
is quite hard and requires lot of money and time.
- So, Now we are using the concept of Cloud Virtual Machines or We use cloud providers
machines like AWS, Azure, GCP, Digital Ocean etc.
How does Container Solves This Problem??
- So to solve the problem of Underutilization of Virtual Machines the concept of Containerization
- Let us understand the Architecture of Docker or Containerization First:-
- They are lightweight in nature because they do not have " complete Operating System".
- Containers use resources form base operating system or from EC2 instances.
- Containers have minimal "Operating System or Base Image".
- They are very easy to ship or transfer as they are lightweight.
